text=%3c%3c|ImperiumEditionIndex|>>%0a%0aA late [[Chronology/FirstDecline|Decline]] mineral exploration company, founded on StarSystems/NovyaSiberia about sixty standard years before hop space travel again became possible, largely to access the resources of that system.%0a%0aWith the return to FTL travel, BFEC became one of the first companies in human space to utilize hop space commercially, not only creating the first exploratory fleet since the Chronology/FirstExpanse, but also opening branch offices on a number of systems.%0a%0aAs Soup travel grew, BFEC became very large and wealthy, but also came under a good deal of scrutiny.  Rumors of forced enslavement of populations on worlds that had become primitive during the Decline circulated.  BFEC denied this, but finally sufficient evidence was gathered and the corporation was forced to admit to the practice, and a number of systems fined it vast sums, so great that the company was finally forced to declare bankruptcy.%0a%0aIt had an afterlife of sorts, its assets being bought out by the [[TawmerikDynasty|Tawmerik Family]] of the [[StarSystems/Vadia]] system.  The name was abandoned, but the fleet and hopspace routes served to make the Tawmeriks one of the wealthiest families in human space, and served ultimately in their ability to undermine the TerranRepublic and transform it into the Imperium.%0a%0a!! References%0a# Chronology/FirstDecline%0a# Chronology/FirstExpanse%0a# StarSystems/NovyaSiberia%0a# TawmerikDynasty%0a# TerranRepublic%0a# [[StarSystems/Vadia|Vadia System]]%0a%0a!! Related Articles%0a(:pagelist group=Macropedia fmt=simple {$Name}:)%0a%0a[[!ImperiumEdition]] [[!ChangSinghAuthored]]
